rComments: Funny, young guy, made class interesting, sometimes unclear on expectations. Easy enough to get a B, only 1 essay.  Requires alot of reading if you want an A.

Awesome. Simple as that. He is fair and concise. He tells you, come to class and read the textbook if you want, it will help you know how to argue etc. I never read it and did just fine. He's got good style too haha Overall, he's helpful and makes a boring class semi-entertaining.

Bioethics was a brutal course. The prof is  approachable and explains the theories well. The marking scheme is harsh considering that we're science students and have never written an ethics paper before. There is too much reading - you're expected to read the whole textbook according to the syllabus which is unrealistic.
